    "text": "We phenotyped 590 diverse sorghum accessions from West Africa in 10 environments under drought stress conditions: preflowering water stress (WS1), postflowering water stress (WS2), well-watered (WW), and rainfed (RF) over 4 years. Traits measured include days to 50% flowering (DFLo), aboveground dry biomass (DBM), plant height (PH), and grain yield components: grain weight (GrW), panicle weight (PW), grain number (GrN) per plant, and 1000-grain weight (TGrW). Genome-wide association studies (GWAS) were conducted. Broad-sense heritability for biomass and grain yield was 33-92% across environments.",
